Computer Lab Hours
The Richland Two Charter High School is open for student use Monday through Thursday, 8:00 AM until 8:00 PM, and Friday until 3:00 PM. The lab will close at 7:10 PM if no students have arrived by that time. Please arrive no later than 6:00 PM to take quizzes. 
Students will not be permitted to log on to a computer after 7:10 PM, as this allows at least thirty (30) minutes to complete any work before having to log out by 7:45 PM. 
The latest start-time for a course exam is 6:45 PM, which allows a one-hour minimum per exam session. 
All computers must be shut down by 7:45 PM  Monday through Thursday. 

Staff Evening Computer Lab Hours 4:00 PM - Until 

Monday: Henry Lovett, Principal
Tuesday: Ann Holland, Work-Based Learning Coordinator
Wednesday: Brian Stiles, English Teacher/Testing Coordinator
Thursday: Angela Bright, School Counselor 

Students: If you are working from home and have questions, please call the computer lab at 803-419-1348, ext. 6. 
 



 













